meanings.definition: To outsmart or outmaneuver in political strategy.
meanings.sent1: She outpoliticked her opponent by using clever tactics during the debate.
meanings.sent2: The senator outpoliticked his rival to win the election.
meanings.sent3: The mayor outpoliticked the city council in passing the new law.
meanings.sent4: The student outpoliticked the teacher by finding a loophole in the school rules.
meanings.sent5: The detective outpoliticked the criminals to solve the case.

meanings.sent1: He had outpoliticked his opponents in the previous election.
meanings.sent2: She outpoliticked her colleagues in the last negotiation.
meanings.sent3: The team outpoliticked their rivals in the final match.
meanings.sent4: The company outpoliticked its competitors to secure the deal.
meanings.sent5: The players outpoliticked the referees to gain an advantage.
